Preheat your #oven to 190 degrees. Cut the ends off the @Echalion Shallot{1}, peel and finely slice. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Remove the top from the @Carrot{2}, peel and grate on the coarse side of your #grater. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{125%g}.

Heat a wide bottomed #saucepan{} over high heat and add a splash of @oil{some}. Cook the @British Beef Mince{500%g} for ~{5%minutes} until browned and then stir in your shallot and garlic. Cook for a further ~{3%minutes} until your shallot is soft. Add your carrot and the @Provencal Herbs{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the tinned @Cherry Tomatoes{1}(tinned), @Tomato Passata{1}, @Worcester Sauce{1} and @Beef Stock Pot{1} and @Water{350%ml}. Mix well and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat until your bolognese is gently bubbling, cook for ~{15%minutes} uncovered. Once your bolognese is nice and thick, remove the pan from the heat and cover.

While your bolognese is simmering, place your @Purple Sprouting Broccoli{2} on a #baking tray{} and cover the tray tightly with #foil. Pop on the top shelf of your #oven for ~{12-15%minutes}.

> This allows the broccoli to steam in the oven!

Whilst everything is cooking you can get on with the gnocchi! Add a splash of @oil{some} to a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the @Gnocchi{500%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and cook for ~{11%minutes} or until lightly golden on the outside and fluffy on the inside.

> You may wish to do this in batches!

Remove your broccoli from your #oven and preheat your #grill{} to high. Remove the foil covering, sprinkle your cheese over your broccoli and grill for ~{2-4%minutes} or until nice and golden.

> You might like to leave a few tablespoons of grated cheese to the side for sprinkling over your bolognese later!

Roughly tear the @Basil{1}(leaves roughly torn) and stir them into your bolognese. Now add your gnocchi and season with @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste}. Remove your cheesy broccoli from under your grill and serve alongside your gnocchi bolognese.

Buon Appetito!